 Let $p$ represent the popularity of the toaster (or the number of customers who buy it), and $c$ denote the cost of the toaster. Daniel's theory implies an inverse proportionality between $p$ and $c$, such that their product equals a constant $k$. Given that $p=12$ when $c=500$, we find $k=(12)(500)=6000$. Therefore, when $c=750$,

