By dividing the axes into 60 units, the shaded area can be divided into a triangle with an area of $20\cdot 20/2=200$ square units and a parallelogram with an area of $20\cdot 40=800$ square units. The entire square has an area of 3600 square units. The ratio becomes $1000/3600=\boxed{\frac{5}{18}}$.
